	heroObjectPosition={`center center`}
	directAnswerHtml={`<strong style="color: var(--color-ink);">If money is tight and the weight is heavy, the Father's Heart Bible™ is for you.</strong> Bible verses for financial hardship aren't a promise that the struggle disappears overnight — they're an anchor for the days the paycheck doesn't stretch, the debt feels endless, and the financial stress steals your sleep. The <a href="https://fathersheartbible.com/read" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">Father's Heart Bible™</a> is a fresh English translation you can read and <em>listen to</em> free on your phone — and it reveals God as a <em>Father</em> who feeds the birds, knows your needs before you ask, and provides. Whether you searched "Bible verses for financial hardship," "what does the Bible say about debt," or "does God care about my finances" — the answer starts here: your worth was never your bank balance. You are His beloved child, and He will not leave you.`}
	keyTakeaway={`God is your Father, and He knows what you need. The Bible doesn't shame you for falling behind — it points you to a Provider who feeds the birds, opens His hand, and promises never to leave you. Your worth is not your bank balance; it's your belonging to Him.`}
	painsHeading={`The weight of financial hardship`}
	painsIntroHtml={`If you're stretched thin, behind on bills, or lying awake doing the math, you are not failing and you are not alone. Millions of households are carrying the same weight right now — and the numbers say it out loud.`}
	painStats={[
		{ value: `37%`, label: `of U.S. adults could not fully cover a surprise $400 expense with cash — 13% couldn't pay it by any means (Federal Reserve SHED, 2023)` },
		{ value: `13%`, label: `of adults said they would be unable to pay a $400 emergency expense by any means at all (Federal Reserve SHED, 2023)` },
		{ value: `66%`, label: `of U.S. adults say money is a significant source of stress (APA, Stress in America)` },
		{ value: `57%`, label: `of money-stressed adults say paying for the present — food, rent, the basics — is their main money worry (APA)` },
		{ value: `13.5%`, label: `of U.S. households — 47.4 million people — were food insecure at some point in 2023 (USDA)` },
		{ value: `1 in 3`, label: `single-mother households with children faced food insecurity in 2023 (USDA)` },
	]}
	painsBodyHtml={`<p>Behind every statistic is a real family — maybe yours. The paycheck that's gone before the month is. The card you swipe hoping it clears. The job that ended without warning. The grocery run where you put things back. The shame of a bill marked past due, and the worry that follows you into the night.</p><p>None of this means you've failed as a person. It means you're living in a season — or a system — where the cost of survival outpaces the income, and that is a weight no one was built to carry alone. There is a Father who sees the bills and the worry, who knows what you need before you ask, and who has something to say about who you are underneath the numbers.</p>`}
	painsSources={[
		{ label: `Federal Reserve — Economic Well-Being of U.S. Households in 2023 (Expenses)`, url: `https://www.federalreserve.gov/publications/2024-economic-well-being-of-us-households-in-2023-expenses.htm` },
		{ label: `USDA ERS — Household Food Security in the United States in 2023`, url: `https://www.ers.usda.gov/publications/pub-details?pubid=109895` },
		{ label: `American Psychological Association — Stress in America`, url: `https://www.apa.org/news/press/releases/stress/2022/concerned-future-inflation` },
	]}
	aFatherHeading={`A Father for those facing financial hardship`}
	aFatherBodyHtml={`<p>Here's what almost no one tells you in the middle of a money crisis: the deepest answer to financial hardship isn't only a bigger income or a cleared balance — though God can and does provide for real needs. The answer underneath the answer is a <strong style="color: var(--color-ink);">Father</strong> — one who knows exactly what you need and has never once forgotten you.</p><p>Jesus pointed to the birds: they don't store up in barns, yet your heavenly Father feeds them. And He said you are worth far more than they are. You were not made to earn your worth by your provision for yourself. You were made to be provided for by a Father whose hand is open and whose love is not measured in dollars.</p><p>So before you are a paycheck, a credit score, a provider stretched to the edge — you are His. Your Father wants to be the steady ground under your feet when the finances shake, the voice that says: I see the bills, I know the need, I have not left you, and your worth was never your wallet.</p>`}
