	voiceIntroHtml={`Nine Bible verses for financial hardship in the Father's Heart Bible™ — each one a word from your Provider Father, straight into the place where money is tight. Tap any reference to read and listen free.`}
	verses={[
		{ ref: `Matthew 6:31-33`, slug: `matthew`, ch: 6, text: `So do not worry, saying, 'What will we eat?' or 'What will we drink?' Your Father knows that you need them all. Seek first His kingdom and His righteousness, and all these things will be given to you as well.`, note: `Your Father already knows the need behind the worry — you're not informing Him, you're trusting Him.` },
		{ ref: `Matthew 6:25-26`, slug: `matthew`, ch: 6, text: `Look at the birds of the air; they neither sow nor reap nor gather into barns, and yet your heavenly Father feeds them. Are you not of more value than they?`, note: `If He feeds the birds, He has not overlooked you. You are worth more to your Father than you know.` },
		{ ref: `Philippians 4:19`, slug: `philippians`, ch: 4, text: `And my God will supply every need of yours according to His riches in glory in Christ Jesus.`, note: `Not your wants on demand, but your real needs, met from a supply that never runs dry.` },
		{ ref: `Psalm 23:1`, slug: `psalms`, ch: 23, text: `The Lord is my shepherd; I shall not want.`, note: `When everything feels uncertain, He is the Shepherd who makes sure you lack nothing you truly need.` },
		{ ref: `Proverbs 3:5-6`, slug: `proverbs`, ch: 3, text: `Trust in the Lord with all your heart, and do not lean on your own understanding; in all your ways acknowledge Him, and He will make your paths straight.`, note: `When you can't see how the math works out, hand the road to the Father and let Him direct it.` },
		{ ref: `Psalm 37:25`, slug: `psalms`, ch: 37, text: `I have been young, and now am old, yet I have not seen the righteous forsaken or their children begging for bread.`, note: `A lifetime of evidence: your Father does not abandon His own to go without.` },
		{ ref: `Hebrews 13:5`, slug: `hebrews`, ch: 13, text: `Keep your life free from the love of money, and be content with what you have, for your Father has said, "I will never leave you nor forsake you."`, note: `Whatever the balance reads, the one thing you cannot lose is Him — and He has promised never to go.` },
		{ ref: `Luke 12:24`, slug: `luke`, ch: 12, text: `Consider the ravens: they neither sow nor reap, they have neither storehouse nor barn, and yet your Father feeds them. Of how much more value are you than the birds!`, note: `Even the birds with no savings are fed. Your Father counts you far more precious than they.` },
		{ ref: `2 Corinthians 9:8`, slug: `2-corinthians`, ch: 9, text: `And God is able to make all grace abound to you, so that in all things, at all times, having all that you need, you will abound in every good work.`, note: `His grace meets you with enough — not so you hoard it, but so you have what you need and more to give.` },
