	voicesIntroHtml={`When money is short, the worry can drown out everything. The truth beneath every verse here — that God is, before anything else, a Father who feeds the birds and knows what you need — is the one these voices gave their lives to:`}
	voices={[
		{ quote: `Answered prayer is the interchange of love between the Father and His child.`, name: `Andrew Murray`, role: `who taught a generation to live as the Father's children`, photo: `https://cdn.sanity.io/images/rusi1hyi/production/133bc45cfa954cf1ae99b7afac5954eca764ed70-500x830.jpg` },
		{ quote: `The hardest, gladdest thing in the world is, to cry Father! from a full heart.`, name: `George MacDonald`, role: `who taught that the Fatherhood of God is the heart of the gospel`, photo: `https://cdn.sanity.io/images/rusi1hyi/production/35e71c2610893383d20b60883aa0b1d4d4664cbc-500x726.jpg` },
		{ quote: `There is heaven in the depth of that word — Father.`, name: `Charles Spurgeon`, role: `the “Prince of Preachers”`, photo: `https://cdn.sanity.io/images/rusi1hyi/production/e48a128da123135241be9c95cf35b37498d94ea5-500x617.jpg` },
	]}
	voicesCreditHtml={`Photos via <a href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" style="color: var(--color-brand);" class="hover:underline">Wikimedia Commons</a> &mdash; Andrew Murray, George MacDonald, and Charles Spurgeon (all public domain).`}
	wordHeading={`His Word will not return void`}
	wordBodyHtml={`<p>You might not feel the weight lift the first time you read it. That's okay. The Father's provision isn't a hype feeling — it's a foundation, and foundations get built quietly, one day at a time. Every verse you take in is your Father planting something in you that the hardship can't uproot: His presence, His promise, your worth in Him.</p><p class="mt-4" style="color: var(--color-ink);">"My word… will not return to me empty, but will accomplish that which I purpose." <span style="color: var(--color-muted);">— Isaiah 55:11</span></p>`}
	fatherSaysHeading={`What your Father says over you`}
	fatherSaysHtml={`<p>"I see the bills stacked on the counter and the worry you carry to bed. I know what you need before you ask Me — the rent, the groceries, the way forward — none of it is hidden from Me. And I want you to hear Me over the fear: your worth was never your wallet. You are not behind in My eyes. You are Mine.</p><p>I feed the birds who store up nothing, and I count you far more precious than they. So bring Me the need, not the shame. I am your Provider, and I will not leave you nor forsake you. Trust Me one day at a time. I am your Father, your portion, and your true inheritance — and I am with you in this."</p>`}
	prayerHeading={`A prayer for those facing financial hardship`}
	prayerHtml={`<p>Our Father, we thank You for these who are carrying a heavy financial weight — every person stretched thin, behind on bills, or lying awake doing the math. You are Jehovah-Jireh, the God who provides; You feed the birds of the air, and You have not forgotten a single one of these Your children. We ask You to meet their real needs — the rent, the food, the bills, the way forward — according to Your riches and not their lack.</p><p>Father, lift the shame and the fear that cling to hardship. Remind them their worth is not their bank balance but their belonging to You. Give them wisdom with what they have, open doors for honest work, and guard them from despair on the hard days and from the love of money on the good ones. Protect them from the lie that they are failing, and from the enemy who would use the pressure to drive them from You instead of to You.</p><p>Let them know You will never leave them nor forsake them, that You are near to the brokenhearted, and that You Yourself are their true inheritance — richer than anything money could buy. Steady their hearts, provide their daily bread, and let them rest tonight in the arms of a Father who sees them and stays.</p><p>In Jesus' name, amen.</p>`}
