	faqs={[
		{ question: `What are good Bible verses for financial hardship?`, answer: `Matthew 6:31-33 (your Father knows what you need), Matthew 6:25-26 (He feeds the birds — you're worth more), Philippians 4:19 (God will supply every need), Psalm 23:1 (the Lord is my shepherd, I shall not want), Proverbs 3:5-6 (trust Him with your path), Psalm 37:25 (the righteous are not forsaken), Hebrews 13:5 (I will never leave you), and 2 Corinthians 9:8 (His grace gives you enough) all speak straight into financial hardship. Read and hear them free in the Father's Heart Bible™ at fathersheartbible.com/read.` },
		{ question: `What does the Bible say about money problems and debt?`, answer: `The Bible takes money problems seriously without shaming the person carrying them. It urges honesty and wisdom with what you have, warns against the love of money (Hebrews 13:5), and points debt-weary people to a Provider rather than a quick fix. Above all it reframes worth: you are not your balance. The Father's Heart Bible™ reveals God as a Father who knows your needs and stays with you through the hard season — read those passages free, with audio, at fathersheartbible.com/read.` },
		{ question: `Is there a Bible verse about provision and trusting God with my finances?`, answer: `Yes. Philippians 4:19 promises that God will supply every need of yours according to His riches, and Matthew 6:33 invites you to seek Him first and trust that your Father knows what you need. Proverbs 3:5-6 adds: trust Him with all your heart and let Him direct your path. These aren't prosperity-gospel guarantees of wealth — they're an anchor for trusting a faithful Provider. Read them free in the Father's Heart Bible™.` },
		{ question: `Does God care about my finances?`, answer: `Yes — deeply. Jesus said your heavenly Father feeds the birds of the air and that you are worth far more than they are (Matthew 6:26). He knows what you need before you ask. God isn't distant from your bills; He is a Father who sees the shortfall, cares about your real needs, and promises never to leave you. In the Father's Heart Bible™ you meet that God as a Father, not a far-off judge.` },
		{ question: `Is there a free Bible with audio I can read when money is tight?`, answer: `Yes. The Father's Heart Bible™ is free to read and listen to online — no account, no purchase, no app. When nothing is what you have, this costs nothing. Open fathersheartbible.com/read on your phone and read or hear any book, perfect for listening during a commute, a job search, or a sleepless night.` },
		{ question: `What makes the Father's Heart Bible™ different for someone in financial hardship?`, answer: `It's the first English translation to reveal God as Father wherever Scripture reveals Him as Father — so instead of reading one more voice about doing better with money, you meet the One who feeds the birds and knows your needs. For someone stretched thin and ashamed of falling behind, that reframes everything: you come to the Bible as a loved child whose worth was never your wallet, not a debtor to be judged.` },
	]}
